    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>VII</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>152f</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>006500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="πολύστροφος">πολύστροφος</w> <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem>πολύστροφος <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg type="alternative"><name nymRef="#Πολύστροφος">Πολύστροφος</name> <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <note>also possible</note></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">πολύστροφος <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمه بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Published from Oliverio papers, without dimensions.</p>
                <p>From the drawing, it is possible to catch an oblique stroke pertaining to the last preserved letter, not transcribed by Pugliese Carratelli.</p>
                <p>Without context, it is impossible to choose between the adjective <foreign xml:lang="grc">πολύστροφος</foreign> ('much-twisted; versatile; making many turns'),
                    a personal name (<foreign xml:lang="grc">Πολύστροφος</foreign>, cf .<bibl><ptr target="#meritt-traill1974"/>, p. <citedRange>11</citedRange></bibl>, 
                    name of a counsellor, ca. 400/350) or a divine name or epithet (so <bibl><ptr target="#marengo1991"/>, p. <citedRange>586</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
